7 February 2007Cabinet held its second meeting of the year in Pretoria today, 7 February 2007. This statement only covers Cabinet decisions other than the policy issues, which will be covered in the President's State of the Nation Address on 9 February in Parliament and the media briefings by Ministers the following week. The meeting considered and approved the government's legislative programme for consideration by Parliament in the 2007 session. The following Bills were approved: The appointment of two Deputy Directors-General (Chief Inspector of Mines; and Corporate Services) in the Department of Minerals and Energy were approved. Enquiries Themba Maseko Cell: 083 645 0810 Issued by: Government Communications (GCIS)top